long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1204602 Kernel trace after gpu hand
Description of problem:
The computer would frequently hang when left alone (most probably while the screen is locked by gdm).
The mouse cursor would still show and move, but on a blank screen. Any other command (keyboard, TTY) are irresponsive and there is no other choice than rebooting.
How reproducible:
It happens often but cannot be reproduced on purpose.
Actual results:
The computer hangs with the mouse cursor on a blank screen.
Expected results:
The lockout gdm screen should show up.
Additional info:
Attached kernel trace shows a lot of error traces.
